# Frontend env — copy to `.env` (local) or `.env.production` (build) to override.
#
# VITE_API_BASE: absolute backend base URL for API calls.
#   - Leave UNSET (default "") in dev → calls are same-origin and go through
#     the Vite proxy (see vite.config.ts). Recommended for local dev/preview.
#   - Set to the backend's PUBLIC url for a cross-origin deploy (app + api on
#     separate hostnames), e.g. behind a Cloudflare Tunnel:
#       VITE_API_BASE=https://api.example.com
#     This is a BUILD-TIME value — it is baked into the bundle by `npm run build`,
#     so put it in `.env.production` and rebuild after changing it. The backend
#     CORS allow-list (VAIC_CORS_ORIGINS) must then include the app origin.
# VITE_API_BASE=https://api.example.com
#
# VITE_ALLOWED_HOSTS: comma-separated Host headers `vite preview`/`vite` accept
# (Vite 8 blocks unknown hosts). Required when serving behind a public hostname
# such as a Cloudflare Tunnel. Read at dev/preview start (not baked into build).
#   VITE_ALLOWED_HOSTS=app.example.com
